verses.verse: The LORD<WH3068> reigneth<WH4427>, he is clothed<WH3847> with majesty<WH1348>; the LORD<WH3068> is clothed<WH3847> with strength<WH5797>, wherewith he hath girded<WH247> himself: the world<WH8398> also is stablished<WH3559>, that it cannot be moved<WH4131>.
Thy throne<WH3678> is established<WH3559> of old<WH227>: thou art from everlasting<WH5769>.
The floods<WH5104> have lifted up<WH5375>, O LORD<WH3068>, the floods<WH5104> have lifted up<WH5375> their voice<WH6963>; the floods<WH5104> lift up<WH5375> their waves<WH1796>.
The LORD<WH3068> on high<WH4791> is mightier<WH117> than the noise<WH6963> of many<WH7227> waters<WH4325>, yea, than the mighty<WH117> waves<WH4867> of the sea<WH3220>.
Thy testimonies<WH5713> are very<WH3966> sure<WH539>: holiness<WH6944> becometh<WH4998> thine house<WH1004>, O LORD<WH3068>, for ever<WH753><WH3117>.
